HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 183
BY REPRESENTATIVE MCMAKIN
A RESOLUTION
To designate Wednesday, April 22, 2026, as LSU Day at the state capitol and to commend
the Louisiana State University System for its enduring contributions to the state of
Louisiana.
WHEREAS, the Louisiana State University System is a family of eight institutions:
the LSU Flagship Campus in Baton Rouge, the LSU Ag Center, the LSU Health Science
Center in New Orleans, the LSU Health Science Center in Shreveport, LSU at Alexandria,
LSU at Eunice, LSU at Shreveport, and Pennington Biomedical Research Center; and
WHEREAS, the University of New Orleans will be joining the LSU System as the
ninth institution under the name LSU at New Orleans in the summer of 2026; and
WHEREAS, under the leadership of President Wade Rousse and Chairman Lee
Mallett and the LSU Board of Supervisors, the LSU System is poised for a new era of
success that is built on the foundational principals of excellence and accessibility; and
WHEREAS, LSU educates more than seventy thousand students annually and
provides top-tier education at campuses in Baton Rouge, New Orleans, Alexandria,
Shreveport, and Eunice; and
WHEREAS, LSU Research expands the frontier of knowledge every single day and
works to bring insight and innovation to the table and create critical solutions to Louisiana's
challenges, including improving health outcomes, preserving the coastline, and expanding
energy production; and
WHEREAS, the LSU Flagship Campus in Baton Rouge, under the leadership of
Chancellor Jim Dalton, has experienced record enrollment and graduation numbers, opened
new educational and research facilities, and seen outstanding achievements by graduates in
academic scholarship and research; and
