WHEREAS, the LSU Ag Center, under the leadership of Senior Vice Chancellor
Matt Lee, ranks twelfth in the nation for research expenditures among academic agricultural
enterprises, educates Louisiana's future leaders through programs such as 4-H, and ensures
that commodities such as sugarcane, rice, and sweet potatoes thrive as the state's
foundational agricultural products; and
WHEREAS, the LSU Health Sciences Center in New Orleans, under the leadership
of Senior Vice Chancellor David Guzick, educates the next generation of Louisiana's
medical professionals, provides outstanding patient care, and works diligently to combat
Louisiana's high rate of cancer deaths through groundbreaking research; and
WHEREAS, the LSU Health Sciences Center in Shreveport, under the leadership of
Senior Vice Chancellor Lester Johnson, brings critical medical care to North Louisiana,
grows its research portfolio to make critical discoveries, and educates doctors, nurses, and
medical professionals who will serve the region for generations to come; and
WHEREAS, Pennington Biomedical Research Center, under the leadership of
Interim Executive Director Jennifer Rood, supports researchers who are working to find the
health solutions of the future and combating Louisiana's nearly forty percent obesity rate
through the development of new diets and revolutionary medications; and
WHEREAS, LSU at Alexandria, under the leadership of Chancellor Paul Coreil, has
experienced record enrollment and created Louisiana's first accelerated bachelor's degrees
in STEM fields to meet critical workforce needs and put students into the workforce faster;
and
WHEREAS, LSU at Shreveport, under the leadership of Chancellor Robert Smith,
has been Louisiana's fastest growing university over the past decade and now graduates more
students than any other university in Louisiana, with the exception of the LSU Flagship
Campus in Baton Rouge; and
WHEREAS, LSU at Eunice, under the leadership of Chancellor Nancee Sorenson,
has experienced record enrollment, leads Louisiana's two year institutions in the number of
students who transfer to bachelor's degree programs, and sees the highest success rate of
those students earning their degrees; and
