WHEREAS, the LSU System celebrates the success of all of its institutions and
proudly supports the Tigers, Bengals, Pilots, Generals, and Privateers as they reach new
heights of accomplishment and break records of achievement; and
WHEREAS, the LSU System, which is united by three letters, two colors, and one
great state, is most deserving of recognition for its outstanding achievements.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
Legislature of Louisiana does hereby designate Wednesday, April 22, 2026, as LSU Day at
the state capitol; does hereby commend the Louisiana State University System for its
enduring contributions to the state of Louisiana; and does hereby extend sincerest
appreciation and support for the system's continued mission and success.
SPEAKER OF THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
